tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE DemographicData (
    user_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    age INT,
    annual_income DECIMAL,
    retirement_goal DECIMAL
)

CREATE TABLE demographic_data (
  user_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  age INT,
  income DECIMAL,
  current_savings DECIMAL,
  retirement_age INT
);
CREATE TABLE retirement_plans (
  plan_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  user_id INT REFERENCES demographic_data(user_id),
  recommended_investment DECIMAL,
  retirement_date DATE,
  risk_tolerance VARCHAR(50)
);

CREATE TABLE retirement_plans (
  plan_id INT,
  plan_name VARCHAR(50),
  description VARCHAR(150),
  group_id INT,
  level_id INT
);

CREATE TABLE AgeGroups (
  group_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  min_age INT,
  max_age INT
)

CREATE TABLE IncomeLevels (
  level_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  min_income DECIMAL(10,2),
  max_income DECIMAL(10,2)
)

CREATE TABLE Customers (
  customer_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  name VARCHAR(50),
  age INT,
  income DECIMAL(10,2),
  group_id INT,
  level_id INT,
  FOREIGN KEY (group_id) REFERENCES AgeGroups(group_id),
  FOREIGN KEY (level_id) REFERENCES IncomeLevels(level_id)
)

CREATE TABLE RetirementPlans (
  plan_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  plan_name VARCHAR(50),
  cost DECIMAL(10,2)
)

CREATE TABLE PlanRecommendations (
  recommendation_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  customer_id INT,
  plan_id INT,
  FOREIGN KEY (customer_id) REFERENCES Customers(customer_id),
  FOREIGN KEY (plan_id) REFERENCES RetirementPlans(plan_id)
)
